Key Match Events: The Kings closed the game with a 19-4 run in the final minutes
De'Aaron Fox scored 14 points in the fourth quarter
De'Aaron Fox shot 81.3% from the field, including 91.7% on two-pointers
Keon Ellis had four steals and two blocks
Post-Match Reflections: Interim coach Doug Christie praised his team's defensive effort
De'Aaron Fox stated, 'Winning at home always puts you in a good spot'
Miscellaneous Highlights: The victory served as a morale boost for the Kings, who had been struggling with late-game collapses earlier in the season
Others: The Sacramento Kings, led by De'Aaron Fox's 35-point performance, rallied from a 14-point deficit to defeat the Philadelphia 76ers 113-107
